(161, 1, '2017-04-07 09:48:34', '2017-04-07 09:48:34', '<em><strong></strong></em>\r\n\r\nMayo Clinic researchers used electrical stimulation on the spinal cord and intense physical therapy to help a man intentionally move his paralyzed legs, stand and make steplike motions for the first time in three years.\r\n\r\nThe 26-year-old patient injured his spinal cord at the sixth thoracic vertebrae in the middle of his back three years earlier. He was diagnosed with a motor complete spinal cord injury, meaning he could not move or feel anything below the middle of his torso.The patient going through 22 weeks of physical therapy.He had three training sesssions a week, He was tested for changes regularly. Some results led researchers to characterize his injury further as discomplete, After a three-week recovery period from surgery, the patient resumed physical therapy with stimulation settings adjusted to enable movements.\r\n\r\nThe first two weeks, he intentionally was able to:\r\n\r\n1 .Control his muscles while lying on his side, resulting in leg movements.\r\n\r\n2 . Make steplike motions while lying on his side and standing with partial support.\r\n\r\n3 .Stand independently using his arms on support bars for balance Intentional, or volitional, movement means the patient\'s brain is sending a signal to motor neurons in his spinal cord to move his legs purposefully.\r\n\r\n<strong>Working:</strong>\r\n\r\nThe electrode is connected to a computer-controlled device under the skin in the patient\'s abdomen. I\'t is a mayo clinic device.\r\nTeams from Mayo Clinic\'s departments of Neurosurgery and Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation, and the Division of Engineering collaborated on this project.\"While these are early results, it speaks to how Mayo Clinic researchers relentlessly pursue discoveries and innovative solutions that address the unmet needs of patients,\" says Gregory Gores.It\'s advances for patient care.\"\r\n\r\n<strong>Use :</strong>\r\nFood and Drug Administration for off-label.', 'Spinal cord using by Man moves paralyzed legs :', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'spinal-cord-using-by-man-moves-paralyzed-legs', '', '', '2017-04-07 09:48:34', '2017-04-07 09:48:34', '', 0, 'http://successfulindia.aypt.in/blog/?p=161', 0, 'post', '', 0),
