(231, 1, '2017-05-23 10:07:12', '2017-05-23 10:07:12', '<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Array destructuring is used to destructuring the variables. This is equivalent to indexing and it was more convenient.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Object destructuring is very useful, because it is used to destructuring the objects within a single line, otherwise requires multiple lines.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The function declaration has tells to the compiler about function name, return type and parameters. When the function is defined then the function has to be called to access the code. Then destructuring is also works in the function declarations.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Spread operator is completely different to destructuring. It is used to spread one array into another array or one object into another object.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Interface contain the declaration of members by deriving a class the member should be defined. The keyword interface is used to declare the interface. Optional property is used in the inter face for each properties are ends with? . Readonly property should not be modify it can be specify before the name of the property.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Interfaces are used to describe the function types. It is similar to function declaration which contains parameter and return type. Each parameter requires both name and type.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A class is used to create one or more objects. It is denoted as class. A function name is same as class name is called.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Inheritance is a process of creating a new class from the existing class. The existing class is called as parent or super class and the newly created class is called as child or sub class. Sub class inherits the properties and a method from the super class except constructor by using extends key word.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When the field and method are denoted as public then it should be visible for all other classes. It can be access from any class.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When the field and method is marked as private then it does not access from other classes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A protected member can be access any classes with the same package and it can be access from the subclass with different package.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Read only modifier can be initialized only in the declaration and in the constructor of same class.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Getter and setter is a way of giving control to access the member of an object.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Static property is used to refer the common property of all objects.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Abstract class cannot be instantiated, but they can be subclassed. An abstract keyword is used to define the abstract class and abstract method.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Function is used to perform a specific task. When the function is defined then it should be called to access the code. The code should be reusable. They are easy to read and maintain. The function type consists of two parts. They are parameter type and return type.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In the rest parameter multiple arguments are passed at the same type.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In the default parameter, the function parameters are set as default. This is a key word that set when the function is called.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A program should have same function name with different implementation is called as function overloading.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Generics are a reusable component we can work over variety of types rather than one. &lt;T&gt; is denoted as a generic type.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Generic class and generic interface has similar shape. They have generic type parameter list in angle brackets (&lt;&gt;).</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Enum is used to define as a set of named numeric constants. It is denoted as enum. The body of the enum consists of 0 or n-1 number of members. Each enum members can be associated with numeric values it can be either constant.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Type inference is used to provide the type of information when there is no explicit type annotation.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The compatibility is based on structural subtyping. I