n&nbsp;\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Inheritance </strong>is a process of creating a new class from the existing class. The existing class is called as parent or super class and the newly created class is called as child or sub class. Sub class inherits the properties and a method from the super class except constructor by using extends key word.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li>When the field and method are denoted as <strong>public</strong> then it should be visible for all other classes. It can be access from any class.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li>When the field and method is marked as <strong>private</strong> then it does not access from other classes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li>A <strong>protected</strong> member can be access any classes with the same package and it can be access from the subclass with different package.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Read only</strong> modifier can be initialized only in the declaration and in the constructor of same class.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Getter and setter</strong> is a way of giving control to access the member of an object.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Static</strong> property is used to refer the common property of all objects.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Abstract </strong>class cannot be instantiated, but they can be subclassed. An <strong>abstract</strong> keyword is used to define the abstract class and abstract method.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Function</strong> is used to perform a specific task. When the function is defined then it should be called to access the code. The code should be reusable. They are easy to read and maintain. The function type consists of two parts. They are parameter type and return type.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li>In the <strong>rest parameter </strong>multiple arguments are passed at the same type.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li>In the <strong>default parameter</strong>, the function parameters are set as default. This is a key word that set when the function is called.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li>A program should have same function name with different implementation is called as <strong>function overloading.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Generics</strong> are a reusable component we can work over variety of types rather than one. &lt;T&gt; is denoted as a generic type.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Generic class </strong>and <strong>generic interface </strong>has similar shape. They have generic type parameter list in angle brackets (&lt;&gt;).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Enum</strong> is used to define as a set of named numeric constants. It is denoted as enum. The body of the enum consists of 0 or n-1 number of members. Each enum members can be associated with numeric values it can be either constant.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Type inference</strong> is used to provide the type of information when there is no explicit type annotation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li>The<strong> compatibility is</strong> based on structural subtyping. It is used to relating the types based on the members.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong> </strong></p>', 'Type Script Day 2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '