yle=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Abstract </strong>class cannot be instantiated, but they can be subclassed. An <strong>abstract</strong> keyword is used to define the abstract class and abstract method.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Function</strong> is used to perform a specific task. When the function is defined then it should be called to access the code. The code should be reusable. They are easy to read and maintain. The function type consists of two parts. They are parameter type and return type.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li>In the <strong>rest parameter </strong>multiple arguments are passed at the same type.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li>In the <strong>default parameter</strong>, the function parameters are set as default. This is a key word that set when the function is called.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li>A program should have same function name with different implementation is called as <strong>function overloading.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong> </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Generics</strong> are a reusable component we can work over variety of types rather than one. &lt;T&gt; is denoted as a generic type.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong> </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Generic class </strong>and <strong>generic interface </strong>has similar shape. They have generic type parameter list in angle brackets (&lt;&gt;).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong> </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Enum</strong> is used to define as a set of named numeric constants. It is denoted as enum. The body of the enum consists of 0 or n-1 number of members. Each enum members can be associated with numeric values it can be either constant.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Type inference</strong> is used to provide the type of information when there is no explicit type annotation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">The<strong> compatibility is</strong> based on structural subtyping. It is used to relating the types based on the members.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Type Script Tutorial Day 2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '231-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-23 10:16:23', '2017-05-23 10:16:23', '', 231, 'http://successfulindia.aypt.in/blog/231-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(237, 1, '2017-05-25 09:12:39', '2017-05-25 09:12:39', '<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"> Enum is used to define as a set of named numeric constants. It is denoted as enum. The body of the enum consists of 0 or n-1 number of members. Each enum members can be associated with numeric values it can be either constant.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Type inference is used to provide the type of information when there is no explicit type annotation.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"> The compatibility is based on structural subtyping. It is used to relating the types based on the members.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"> An intersection type is used to combine multiple types into a single type.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">The type union and the type intersection are closely related, but they are very different. Union is used to combine two or more data types using a pipe symbol. Union is denoted as the type union.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">The type guard has some expressions, they are used to perform a run time check and that are guarantees in some scope. A typeof() type guard is used to get the data type. An instanceof() type guard returns true when the object is created by the given constructor.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"> Alias type is used to create a new name for a type. Objects, arrays, and functions are handled by aliasing.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"> String literal types are used to combine both union, type guards, type aliases.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"> Discriminated Unions are used to combine string literal types, union types, type guards, and type aliases. It is also called as tagged unions or algebraic data types. They are useful for functional programming.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"> Symbol is a primitive data type. It is similar to string and number. By calling a Symbol constructor we can create symbols.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"> Iterator object is not a built-in object, the next method is used to access the next item in the container object. Symbol.iterator function is used to return the list of values. Iterators are allowed only array type values.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"> Modules are executed with their own scope that means variables, functions, classes are declared in the module, they are not visible outside and they are exported explicitly.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"> Using export keyword we can export any type of declaration.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"> An import can be done using the import keyword.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"> Namespacing is used avoid collision to the global namespace. Namespace has big variables that have many properties and methods. Multi-file namespace are used to split the name space.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Type Script Tutorial Day 3', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'type-script-tutorial-day-3', '', '', '2017-05-25 09:12:39', '2017-05-25 09:12:39', '', 0, 'http://successfulindia.aypt.in/blog/?p=237', 0, 'post', '', 0),
