 string and number. By calling a Symbol constructor we can create symbols.\n\n&nbsp;</li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"> Iterator object is not a built-in object, the next method is used to access the next item in the container object. Symbol.iterator function is used to return the list of values. Iterators are allowed only array type values.\n\n&nbsp;</li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"> Modules are executed with their own scope that means variables, functions, classes are declared in the module, they are not visible outside and they are exported explicitly.\n\n&nbsp;</li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"> Using export keyword we can export any type of declaration.\n\n&nbsp;</li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"> An import can be done using the import keyword.\n\n&nbsp;</li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"> Namespacing is used avoid collision to the global namespace. Namespace has big variables that have many properties and methods. Multi-file namespace are used to split the name space.</li>\n</ul>', 'Type Script Tutorial Day 3', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '237-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-25 09:12:37', '2017-05-25 09:12:37', '', 237, 'http://successfulindia.aypt.in/blog/237-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(241, 1, '2017-05-26 09:42:30', '2017-05-26 09:42:30', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\n• Modules are same as namespaces, it contain code and declaration. The main difference is the modules are used to declare their dependencies.\r\n\r\n• Modules are used to provide better code reusability, strong isolation and better tooling support for bundling.\r\n\r\n• If you want to convert a program from namespace to modules then it can be easy to end up with a file using needless namespacing.\r\n\r\n• In the module resolution the compiler shows what the import refers to.\r\n\r\n• --moduleResolution flag is used to specify the module resolution strategy. If not specified, then we can use default resolution strategy called classic.\r\n\r\n• The node resolution strategy attempts to mimic the Node.js module resolution mechanism at the runtime.\r\n\r\n• The declaration merging is used to merging two separate declarations declared with the same name into a single definition.\r\n\r\n• Merging interface is used to joins the members of both declarations into a single interface with the same name.\r\n\r\n• Merging interfaces are similar to merging interfaces, the namespaces of the same name will also merge their members.\r\n\r\n• Namespaces are used to create both a namespace and a value, so we need to understand how both should be merge.\r\n\r\n• JSX is an embeddable xml like syntax. JSX came to popularity with the React framework, but it has seen in other applications as well.\r\n\r\n• Before understanding the type checking with jsx, first you have understood the difference between the intrinsic elements and value-based elements. An intrinsic element are always begins with a lowercase letter, and a value-based element always begins with an uppercase letter.\r\n\r\n• Intrinsic element contains a special interface called JSX.IntrinsicElements. If this interface is not specified, then the intrinsic elements will not be type checked.\r\n\r\n• Value based elements are simply looked up by identifiers that are in scope. It is used to possible to limit the type of a value-based element.', 'TypeScript Tutorial Day 4', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'typescript-tutorial-day-4', '', '', '2017-05-26 09:47:53', '2017-05-26 09:47:53', '', 0, 'http://successfulindia.aypt.in/blog/?p=241', 0, 'post', '', 0),
