(248, 1, '2017-05-30 08:49:38', '2017-05-30 08:49:38', '• The attribute type checking is used to determine the element attribute type. This is little difference between the intrinsic and value-based elements.\r\n\r\n• For intrinsic the type of the property is on JSX.IntrinsicElements.\r\n\r\n• For value-based elements, it is little more complex. It is determined by the type of a property on the element instance type that was previously determined. It property to use is determined by JSX.ElementAttributesProperty.\r\n\r\n• The element attribute type is used to check the attributes in the jsx. It supports optional and required properties.\r\n\r\n• Decorators are used to provide a way to add both annotations and a meta-programming syntax for class declarations and members.\r\n\r\n• A decorator is a special kind of declaration and it can be attached class declaration,method,accessor,property or parameter. The syntax is @ symbol followed by the function.\r\n\r\n• Decorator factory is used return the expression that will be called by the decorator at the run time.\r\n\r\n• Multiple decorators are applied to a single declaration. The expression on each decorator is evaluated from top-bottom. The results are called as function from bottom-top.\r\n\r\n• A class decorator is declared before the class declarations. The class decorator is applied to the constructor of the class and can it be used to observe, modify, or replace the class definition. A class decorator cannot be used in a declaration file.\r\n\r\n• A method decorator is declared before the method declaration. The decorator is applied to the Property Descriptor for the method, and it can be used to observe, modify, or replace the method definition. A method decorator cannot be used in a declaration file, on an overload.\r\n\r\n• Accessor Decorator is declared before an accessor declaration. The accessor decorator is applied to the Property Descriptor for the accessor and it can be used to observe, modify, or replace an accessor’s definitions. An accessor decorator cannot be used in a declaration file.\r\n\r\n• A Property Decorator is declared before a property declaration. A property decorator cannot be used in a declaration file.\r\n\r\n• A Parameter Decorator is declared before a parameter declaration. The parameter decorator is applied to the function for a class constructor or method declaration. It cannot be used in a declaration file and overload.', 'Type Script Tutorial Day 5', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '246-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-30 08:49:38', '2017-05-30 08:49:38', '', 246, 'http://successfulindia.aypt.in/blog/246-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(250, 1, '2017-05-31 09:24:08', '2017-05-31 09:24:08', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">• A mixin is a class that contains methods that can be used by other classes without having the parent class of those other classes.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">• Triple-slash directives are single-line comments and it contains a single XML tag. The comments are used as compiler directives.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">• A triple-slash directive can only be preceded by single or multi-line comments, including other triple-slash directives.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">• The compiler performs a preprocessing pass on input files to resolve all triple-slash reference directives. During this process, the additional files are added to the compilation.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">• Library structure is used to identifying the structure of a library is the first step in writing its declaration file.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">• A global library is one that can be used to access from the global scope. Many libraries are used to expose one or more global variables for their use.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">• A module plugin are used to changes the shape of another module.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">• A global plugin is a global code that are used to changes the shape of some global.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">• A global-modifying module is used to modify the existing values from the global scope when they are imported.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">• Values are runtime names that we can reference in expressions.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">• A namespace declaration can be used to add new types, values, and namespaces in any way which does not create a conflict.</p>', 'Type Script Tutorial Day 6', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'type-script-tutorial-day-6', '', '', '2017-05-31 09:24:08', '2017-05-31 09:24:08', '', 0, 'http://successfulindia.aypt.in/blog/?p=250', 0, 'post', '', 0);
