(453, 1, '2017-09-19 07:25:39', '2017-09-19 07:25:39', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Name of Commission</strong><strong>:- </strong>Staff Selection Commission North Western Region<strong>\r\n</strong><strong>Job Name</strong><strong>:- </strong>Technical Operator, Handicrafts Promotion Officer\r\n<strong>Job Location</strong><strong>:-</strong> Chandigarh</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Technical Operator (Drilling)</strong><strong>:</strong> 41 Vacancies</p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Qualification</strong><strong>:-</strong> Candidates who wanted to participate for SSC NWR Technical Operator job should have Matriculation or equivalent from a recognized Board or University and Certificate from Industrial Training Institute in Motor Mechanic or Diesel Mechanic or Fitter.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Salary Structure</strong><strong>:- </strong>Not Specified</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Handicrafts Promotion Officer</strong><strong>:</strong> 09 vacancies</p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Qualification</strong><strong>:-</strong> Aspirants who decided to join SSC NWR Handicrafts Promotion Officer posts should have Bachelor’s Degree in Design or Fine Arts (Fashion or Textile or Apparel Production) of four years’ duration from a recognized University or Institute with one year experience in field of handicrafts or cottage or small scale industry OR Diploma in Fine Arts (Fashion or Textile Design) of three years’ duration from a recognized University or board or Institute plus two year’s experience in field of handicrafts or cottage or small scale industry.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Salary breakup</strong><strong>:- </strong>Rs. 9300 – 34800/- Grade pay. 4200/- Per Month</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Age Limit</strong><strong>:-</strong> Calculate the Lower and Upper age limit as on 24/09/2017</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-